    <h1>JSON API Documentation</h1>

    <section class="section-intro">
      <p>The CRA FAQ website provides a JSON:API v1.1 compliant REST API for programmatic access to all FAQ content, lists, and guidance requests. All endpoints return a JSON payload with full licensing and source attribution.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Base URL</h2>
      <pre><code>https://cra.orcwg.org/api/v0/</code></pre>
      <aside class="warning">
        <p><strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Version 0 (v0) is unstable and may change.</strong> This API version is experimental and breaking changes may occur without notice. A stable v1 API will be released in the future.</p>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Specification</h2>
      <p>This API follows the <a href="https://jsonapi.org/format/">JSON:API v1.1 specification</a>. All responses include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>jsonapi.version</code> - JSON:API version ("1.1")</li>
        <li><code>data</code> - The primary resource(s)</li>
        <li><code>links</code> - URLs related to the response</li>
        <li><code>meta</code> - Metadata including licensing and timestamps</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Authentication</h2>
      <p><strong>None required.</strong> This is a public, read-only API. All endpoints are freely accessible.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Rate Limiting</h2>
      <p><strong>None.</strong> The API serves pre-generated static JSON files via GitHub Pages CDN. No server-side processing occurs.</p>
    </section>

