    <section>
      <h2>Resource Types</h2>

      <aside class="info">
        <p><strong>üí° Markdown and HTML versions:</strong> Content fields are provided in both markdown (<code>answer</code>, <code>body</code>) and pre-rendered HTML (<code>answerHtml</code>, <code>bodyHtml</code>) formats. The markdown version contains the source with resolved internal links, while the HTML version is ready for direct display. Both include GitHub-flavored markdown alerts.</p>
      </aside>

      <h3>FAQ Resource</h3>
      <p>Represents a single Frequently Asked Question. Includes comprehensive metadata, cross-references to related guidance, and bidirectional links to parent lists.</p>

      <h4>Attributes</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><code>question</code> - The FAQ question in markdown format</li>
        <li><code>questionHtml</code> - The question rendered as HTML</li>
        <li><code>answer</code> - The answer in markdown with resolved internal links</li>
        <li><code>answerHtml</code> - The answer rendered as HTML</li>
        <li><code>answerMissing</code> - Boolean indicating if answer is empty</li>
        <li><code>status</code> - Draft, approved, official, etc.</li>
        <li><code>category</code> - FAQ category/folder name</li>
        <li><code>createdAt</code> - ISO 8601 timestamp of creation</li>
        <li><code>lastUpdatedAt</code> - ISO 8601 timestamp of last update</li>
        <li><code>listed</code> - Boolean indicating if FAQ is in curated lists</li>
        <li><code>relatedIssues</code> - Array of GitHub issue references with url and number</li>
        <li><code>author</code> - Content author attribution</li>
        <li><code>authorUrl</code> - URL to author/contributor page</li>
        <li><code>license</code> - License designation (CC BY 4.0)</li>
        <li><code>licenseUrl</code> - URL to license terms</li>
        <li><code>srcUrl</code> - Link to source in GitHub repository</li>
        <li><code>editOnGithubUrl</code> - Direct edit link to GitHub</li>
        <li><code>guidanceId</code> - Reference to related guidance request (if any)</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Relationships</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><code>parents</code> - Array of parent lists (categories) this FAQ belongs to</li>
        <li><code>relatedGuidanceRequest</code> - Single related guidance request (if guidanceId is set)</li>
      </ul>

